  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Nyiragongo Volcanic eruption in Goma</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">As a result of the various earthquakes felt and recorded, several old fractures, previously covered by old flows or filled in by the population, have reopened. In Goma, the districts affected by this reopening are Mabanga North, Mabanga South, Volcanoes and Bujovu. The provincial authorities ordered the evacuation of 10 of the 18 neighbourhoods in the city of Goma on 27 May 2021. These are the MAJENGO, MABANGA NORTH, MABANGA SOUTH, BUJOVU, VIRUNGA, MURARA, MAPENDO, MIKENO, KAYEMBE and LEVOLCAN districts . Some went to the territories of MASISI and RUTSHURU, while others went to the province of South Kivu and to RWANDA. Those who could not go to these destinations went to Sak&#xE9;, 20 km from the city of Goma, where they are living in collective centres. These displaced people have gathered in 21 collective centres in the localities of LUTOBOGO, KIMOKA, NZULO and MATCHA in the territory of Masisi, in the Northern Province as per the below table. Given that Goma is an endemic zone of Cholera outbreak, there is also a high risk of new cases of cholera and its spread during the displacement. A total of 80 cases, 38 in Sake and 42 in Kirotche have been so far declared. In addition, this crisis occurred amid the COVID -19 pandemic and there might be a risk of new contamination due to the lack of prevention measures.</narrative>
  </description>
